1
00:01:02,017 --> 00:01:03,203
What’s going on?

2
00:01:03,336 --> 00:01:04,520
Why is it so noisy?

3
00:01:04,766 --> 00:01:05,660
Yesterday,

4
00:01:05,738 --> 00:01:08,680
a customer posted a review saying our Pad Thai with fermented rice noodles

5
00:01:08,876 --> 00:01:09,900
was the most delicious ever.

6
00:01:10,130 --> 00:01:12,472
So today we’ve been flooded with orders.

7
00:01:12,554 --> 00:01:13,683
There are so many coming in.

8
00:01:16,092 --> 00:01:17,420
Hello, yes?

9
00:01:17,534 --> 00:01:18,589
Another seven orders?

10
00:01:18,660 --> 00:01:19,160
Of course.

11
00:01:21,206 --> 00:01:22,160
Chef Tai,

12
00:01:22,349 --> 00:01:24,441
the customers just ordered seven more portions.

13
00:01:24,540 --> 00:01:26,698
Seven more? We haven’t even finished the last batch yet.

14
00:01:27,323 --> 00:01:29,060
Should we stop accepting orders?

15
00:01:29,217 --> 00:01:30,140
No, no.

16
00:01:30,254 --> 00:01:32,046
This is a golden opportunity for the homestay.

17
00:01:32,289 --> 00:01:33,026
Exactly.

18
00:01:33,091 --> 00:01:35,780
And all the ingredients come from the villagers too.

19
00:01:35,936 --> 00:01:37,808
The more we can sell,

20
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:39,619
the more we can help the community.

21
00:01:40,001 --> 00:01:40,920
That’s true.

22
00:01:41,827 --> 00:01:44,320
Then I’ll help out too.

23
00:01:44,563 --> 00:01:46,180
Really, Lean?

24
00:01:46,875 --> 00:01:51,040
Of course. I will help a lot.

25
00:01:51,179 --> 00:01:51,679
Come on.

26
00:01:51,679 --> 00:01:53,807
What do you want me to do?

27
00:01:54,005 --> 00:01:54,505
Okay.

28
00:02:08,797 --> 00:02:09,543
Chef!

29
00:02:09,664 --> 00:02:10,891
The sauce is about to burn!

30
00:02:12,565 --> 00:02:14,469
We’re running out of vegetables too.

31
00:02:16,150 --> 00:02:18,862
Lean, could you grab more vegetables from inside?

32
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:21,334
Then who’s going to watch the sauce?

33
00:02:24,354 --> 00:02:25,200
I can’t.

34
00:02:25,781 --> 00:02:27,349
I have to prepare the ingredients.

35
00:02:27,420 --> 00:02:30,654
The delivery guy has been waiting for a while already.

36
00:02:30,995 --> 00:02:32,586
I have to go first.

37
00:02:44,175 --> 00:02:44,675
Hey!

38
00:02:47,330 --> 00:02:47,939
You there.

39
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:50,380
Yes, you.

40
00:02:51,575 --> 00:02:52,720
How much longer are you going to sit there?

41
00:02:57,784 --> 00:02:58,360
Hey...

42
00:02:59,657 --> 00:03:00,919
How much longer are you staying there?

43
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:05,520
Me?

44
00:03:06,793 --> 00:03:07,293
Well...

45
00:03:07,952 --> 00:03:08,900
probably a while.

46
00:03:09,251 --> 00:03:11,654
I haven’t gotten very far with my writing yet.

47
00:03:14,621 --> 00:03:17,040
That’s not what I meant. I mean...

48
00:03:18,079 --> 00:03:19,342
everyone else is busy like this,

49
00:03:19,563 --> 00:03:21,563
and you still don’t plan on getting up to help?

50
00:03:23,521 --> 00:03:24,300
I’m sorry.

51
00:03:24,893 --> 00:03:28,903
I’m a writer, not a chef.

52
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,900
We don’t need a writer.

53
00:03:32,841 --> 00:03:34,774
We need every kind of labor we can get.

54
00:03:34,902 --> 00:03:36,902
At this point, if you’re a living being,

55
00:03:37,645 --> 00:03:38,573
we need you.

56
00:03:41,464 --> 00:03:43,762
If it’s manual labor,

57
00:03:44,447 --> 00:03:47,008
I’m probably not much help.

58
00:03:47,534 --> 00:03:48,034
Hmm.

59
00:03:48,683 --> 00:03:50,680
So you can’t do anything at all?

60
00:03:52,635 --> 00:03:53,600
Don’t underestimate me.

61
00:03:54,297 --> 00:03:56,900
When I was little, I helped my mom cook all the time.

62
00:03:58,312 --> 00:03:58,812
Oh?

63
00:03:59,221 --> 00:04:00,220
What can you do?

64
00:04:01,624 --> 00:04:02,440
Well...

65
00:04:03,462 --> 00:04:05,792
I can wash vegetables and peel garlics.

66
00:04:06,262 --> 00:04:07,380
Mm-hmm.

67
00:04:07,873 --> 00:04:08,784
Then...

68
00:04:09,122 --> 00:04:11,700
why don’t you show me your skills?

69
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:17,899
Are these two going to flirt forever?

70
00:04:18,083 --> 00:04:18,583
Oops, I mean—

71
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:21,200
are you going to keep fighting, or help me first?

72
00:04:27,188 --> 00:04:30,120
If you’re really that capable, then show me what you can do.

73
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:43,940
Hey.

74
00:04:44,351 --> 00:04:46,000
Why aren’t you arranging the plates from left to right?

75
00:04:46,157 --> 00:04:48,000
If you do it like this, everyone will get confused while serving.

76
00:04:48,157 --> 00:04:49,080
Geez.

77
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:51,685
Things are already chaotic and you’re still giving orders.

78
00:04:52,498 --> 00:04:53,520
Haven’t you heard?

79
00:04:53,905 --> 00:04:56,260
Organization is the basic of every job.

80
00:04:56,414 --> 00:04:57,540
Even in chaos!!

81
00:04:57,796 --> 00:05:00,560
if they’re not arranged properly, how will we know which plate has shrimp and which has pork?

82
00:05:00,858 --> 00:05:01,840
Wow.

83
00:05:02,514 --> 00:05:04,080
Fine, whatever you say.

84
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:08,340
But first, try cutting the vegetables beautifully and symmetrically.

85
00:05:08,799 --> 00:05:09,299
Hmph.

86
00:05:09,673 --> 00:05:11,137
Like you’re so good at it yourself.

87
00:05:11,491 --> 00:05:13,320
Even squirrels would break their teeth trying to eat these.

88
00:05:13,866 --> 00:05:14,366
Oh?

89
00:05:16,422 --> 00:05:17,920
Have you ever even been in a kitchen before?

90
00:05:31,286 --> 00:05:33,788
Chef, are they really helping us?

91
00:05:34,066 --> 00:05:35,620
I’m not so sure myself.

92
00:05:36,014 --> 00:05:36,514
Hmm.

93
00:05:36,792 --> 00:05:37,880
Can you really handle this?

94
00:05:47,843 --> 00:05:48,343
Yay!

95
00:05:48,435 --> 00:05:51,099
We finally finished everything in time.

96
00:05:51,580 --> 00:05:53,360
Thank you, everyone.

97
00:05:53,740 --> 00:05:56,780
Especially these two, who seemed to bicker nonstop,

98
00:05:56,886 --> 00:05:58,702
but actually helped a lot.

99
00:05:59,491 --> 00:06:01,140
Bickering, Fah?

100
00:06:01,552 --> 00:06:03,116
I call it...

101
00:06:03,185 --> 00:06:04,380
driving force.

102
00:06:04,864 --> 00:06:07,200
Powered by sound waves.

103
00:06:07,446 --> 00:06:09,440
Wow.

104
00:06:10,003 --> 00:06:12,240
More like the kind of sound waves that make people want to cover their ears.

105
00:06:12,699 --> 00:06:15,540
At least it turned out better than expected, didn’t it?

106
00:06:16,165 --> 00:06:16,790
See?

107
00:06:16,938 --> 00:06:17,500
See?

108
00:06:17,850 --> 00:06:19,340
When you stop overthinking,

109
00:06:19,429 --> 00:06:21,963
it works better than relying on theories.

110
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:24,160
But some things need thought, don’t they?

111
00:06:24,429 --> 00:06:26,340
That way you know if it’s really right.

112
00:06:27,894 --> 00:06:29,000
But something...

113
00:06:29,382 --> 00:06:31,800
you know the answer just by doing them.

114
00:06:33,430 --> 00:06:34,080
Then...

115
00:06:34,559 --> 00:06:36,160
I’ll try not to think so much.

116
00:06:36,252 --> 00:06:38,252
And just follow my heart instead.

117
00:06:38,781 --> 00:06:39,281
Oh?

118
00:06:40,268 --> 00:06:41,720
Don’t say things like that.

119
00:06:42,001 --> 00:06:43,700
You’ll make people misunderstand.

120
00:06:43,909 --> 00:06:46,160
Like you’re confessing your feelings to me.

121
00:06:48,306 --> 00:06:50,020
If you keep joking like that,

122
00:06:50,268 --> 00:06:51,380
be careful...

123
00:06:51,764 --> 00:06:53,100
it might come true.

124
00:06:53,743 --> 00:06:56,260
You really want to win against me that badly, huh?

125
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:57,500
Wait.

126
00:06:57,659 --> 00:06:59,800
I thinks there’s no winning or losing here.

127
00:06:59,901 --> 00:07:01,620
There’s only the one who falls first.

128
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,080
What kind of person puts noodles on their head?

129
00:07:25,636 --> 00:07:27,940
I used to think love had to be calm

130
00:07:28,005 --> 00:07:29,200
to feel safe.

131
00:07:29,522 --> 00:07:32,762
But actually, arguing

132
00:07:32,917 --> 00:07:34,749
or even misunderstanding each other...

133
00:07:35,278 --> 00:07:36,809
they make us realize

134
00:07:36,971 --> 00:07:38,971
that we still want to be part of the same story.

135
00:07:39,568 --> 00:07:41,568
Because when everything becomes completely silent,

136
00:07:42,046 --> 00:07:43,280
that may not be peace.

137
00:07:43,831 --> 00:07:46,980
It may just mean we’re no longer in each other’s hearts.

138
00:08:35,628 --> 00:08:36,128
Hey.

139
00:08:37,311 --> 00:08:38,540
You’re still awake?

140
00:08:40,335 --> 00:08:40,835
Yeah.

141
00:08:41,533 --> 00:08:43,040
I can’t write anything.

142
00:08:44,795 --> 00:08:46,121
Your book?

143
00:08:47,759 --> 00:08:48,300
Mm.

144
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:52,780
I feel like...

145
00:08:53,383 --> 00:08:56,480
the more I try to write from real emotions,

146
00:08:57,128 --> 00:08:59,420
the quieter my mind becomes.

147
00:09:01,660 --> 00:09:04,220
The voice in my head

148
00:09:05,213 --> 00:09:06,980
can’t explain anything anymore.

149
00:09:08,228 --> 00:09:09,100
I think...

150
00:09:09,874 --> 00:09:11,460
maybe you should rest for a while.

151
00:09:11,875 --> 00:09:13,240
Sometimes the heart

152
00:09:13,475 --> 00:09:15,740
just needs a little rest too.

153
00:09:27,569 --> 00:09:28,749
Have you ever thought

154
00:09:30,038 --> 00:09:32,840
that maybe we don’t have to understand every feeling?

155
00:09:33,990 --> 00:09:35,990
Just knowing they’re real is enough.

156
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:39,840
That’s exactly

157
00:09:40,062 --> 00:09:41,141
what I’m afraid of.

158
00:09:42,198 --> 00:09:43,060
Afraid that

159
00:09:43,966 --> 00:09:45,680
if I feel too much,

160
00:09:46,102 --> 00:09:47,620
I won’t be able to keep writing.

161
00:09:50,603 --> 00:09:52,683
Afraid you won’t be able to keep writing

162
00:09:53,846 --> 00:09:54,720
or afraid...

163
00:09:55,847 --> 00:09:58,065
that your feelings are actually real?

164
00:10:02,136 --> 00:10:03,300
Maybe...

165
00:10:04,261 --> 00:10:06,540
it’s both.

166
00:10:08,940 --> 00:10:11,600
You don’t have to be strong all the time, Tymn.

167
00:10:13,506 --> 00:10:17,166
You talk like you’ve never been afraid of anything.

168
00:10:20,170 --> 00:10:21,666
I’m afraid of a lot of things.

169
00:10:24,364 --> 00:10:26,660
But you seem like

170
00:10:27,241 --> 00:10:29,241
someone who’s never afraid of anything.

171
00:10:31,619 --> 00:10:33,846
Everyone has something they’re afraid of.

172
00:10:35,219 --> 00:10:36,380
Actually...

173
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:39,960
I’m afraid of staying in this house alone.

174
00:10:40,872 --> 00:10:41,980
Because this house...

175
00:10:42,707 --> 00:10:45,000
holds memories I don’t want to remember.

176
00:10:47,283 --> 00:10:48,800
Every sound in this house...

177
00:10:49,784 --> 00:10:51,180
whether it’s

178
00:10:52,058 --> 00:10:53,680
the faucet,

179
00:10:54,610 --> 00:10:55,860
the rain,

180
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:58,780
or the doors opening and closing...

181
00:11:01,228 --> 00:11:02,560
those sounds...

182
00:11:04,923 --> 00:11:08,700
they keep reminding me that silence never truly comforts anyone.

183
00:11:14,197 --> 00:11:15,140
Then...

184
00:11:16,137 --> 00:11:17,149
right now,

185
00:11:18,407 --> 00:11:20,100
are you still afraid?

186
00:11:22,094 --> 00:11:23,360
Mmm....

187
00:11:25,675 --> 00:11:27,675
Actually, not as much anymore.

188
00:11:29,721 --> 00:11:30,840
Because now,

189
00:11:31,872 --> 00:11:33,168
there’s something

190
00:11:33,740 --> 00:11:35,740
that feels warmer...

191
00:11:36,706 --> 00:11:37,300
right here.

192
00:11:46,536 --> 00:11:47,856
You may not know it,

193
00:11:49,335 --> 00:11:50,160
but

194
00:11:51,622 --> 00:11:53,622
I'm really feeling warmer.

195
00:12:14,186 --> 00:12:17,077
Sometimes, the thing that scares us most

196
00:12:17,585 --> 00:12:18,982
isn’t being misunderstood.

197
00:12:19,585 --> 00:12:21,903
It’s being understood too well...

198
00:12:22,431 --> 00:12:23,720
so well that we’re afraid

199
00:12:24,263 --> 00:12:26,820
there’s nowhere left to hide our feelings.

200
00:12:27,213 --> 00:12:29,280
And on the day we let someone

201
00:12:29,429 --> 00:12:31,094
see our vulnerable part,

202
00:12:31,362 --> 00:12:33,898
that’s when we realize true relationships

203
00:12:34,233 --> 00:12:36,000
don’t need explanations.

204
00:12:36,234 --> 00:12:38,680
They just need someone to stay

205
00:12:38,896 --> 00:12:41,720
when we’re not strong enough to smile.

